    "As roughly 20% of Flan consists of examples from SUPER-NATURALINSTRUCTIONS, our evaluation of Llama-2 instruction-tuned models is likely affected by data contamination (Magar and Schwartz, 2022).",
    "Still, our results show both 7B and 13B chat models exhibit extensive label bias, possibly due to later fine-tuning on other data.",
    "As it is unclear from the implementation details of Touvron et al. (2023) which exact instances in SUPER-NATURALINSTRUCTIONS were included in train-ing, we do not take extra steps in attempt to reduce possible overlap and contamination.",
    "We evaluate the effects of three label bias mitigation methods: two calibration methods designed to correct a model's label bias by adjusting its output scores; and few-shot LoRA fine-tuning (Hu et al., 2022), which adapts the model to the task and its label distribution.",
    "We describe the methods below."
  ],
